2.1 Type 1

df<- type_1_markers %>% arrange(desc(avg_log2FC))


df2 <- df %>% filter(p_val_adj < 0.05)


DEG_list <- df2

markers <- DEG_list %>% mutate(SYMBOL = gene)


ENTREZ_list <- bitr(
  geneID = DEG_list$gene,
  fromType = "SYMBOL",
  toType = "ENTREZID",
  OrgDb = org.Mm.eg.db
)
## 'select()' returned 1:1 mapping between keys and columns
## Warning in bitr(geneID = DEG_list$gene, fromType = "SYMBOL", toType =
## "ENTREZID", : 1.28% of input gene IDs are fail to map...
markers <-  ENTREZ_list %>% inner_join(markers, by = "SYMBOL")

# Removing genes that are not statistically significant. 
markers <-  markers %>% dplyr::filter(p_val_adj < 0.005)
#head(markers, n = 50)

pos.markers <-  markers %>% dplyr::filter(avg_log2FC > 0.6) %>%  arrange(desc(abs(avg_log2FC)))
#head(pos.markers, n = 50)

pos.ranks <- pos.markers$ENTREZID[abs(pos.markers$avg_log2FC) > 0]
#head(pos.ranks)

pos_go <- enrichGO(gene = pos.ranks,           #a vector of entrez gene id
                   OrgDb = "org.Mm.eg.db",    
                   ont = "BP",
                   readable = TRUE)              #whether mapping gene ID to gene Name

pos_go

2.3 Type 3

df<- type_3_markers %>% arrange(desc(avg_log2FC))


df2 <- df %>% filter(p_val_adj < 0.05)


DEG_list <- df2

markers <- DEG_list %>% mutate(SYMBOL = gene)


ENTREZ_list <- bitr(
  geneID = DEG_list$gene,
  fromType = "SYMBOL",
  toType = "ENTREZID",
  OrgDb = org.Mm.eg.db
)
## 'select()' returned 1:1 mapping between keys and columns
## Warning in bitr(geneID = DEG_list$gene, fromType = "SYMBOL", toType =
## "ENTREZID", : 3.27% of input gene IDs are fail to map...
markers <-  ENTREZ_list %>% inner_join(markers, by = "SYMBOL")

# Removing genes that are not statistically significant. 
markers <-  markers %>% dplyr::filter(p_val_adj < 0.05)
#head(markers, n = 50)

pos.markers <-  markers %>% dplyr::filter(avg_log2FC > 3.5) %>%  arrange(desc(abs(avg_log2FC)))
#head(pos.markers, n = 50)

pos.ranks <- pos.markers$ENTREZID[abs(pos.markers$avg_log2FC) > 0]
#head(pos.ranks)

pos_go <- enrichGO(gene = pos.ranks,           #a vector of entrez gene id
                   OrgDb = "org.Mm.eg.db",    
                   ont = "BP",
                   readable = TRUE)              #whether mapping gene ID to gene Name

pos_go

2.4 Type 4

df<- type_4_markers %>% arrange(desc(avg_log2FC))


df2 <- df %>% filter(p_val_adj < 0.05)


DEG_list <- df2

markers <- DEG_list %>% mutate(SYMBOL = gene)


ENTREZ_list <- bitr(
  geneID = DEG_list$gene,
  fromType = "SYMBOL",
  toType = "ENTREZID",
  OrgDb = org.Mm.eg.db
)
## 'select()' returned 1:1 mapping between keys and columns
## Warning in bitr(geneID = DEG_list$gene, fromType = "SYMBOL", toType =
## "ENTREZID", : 6.25% of input gene IDs are fail to map...
markers <-  ENTREZ_list %>% inner_join(markers, by = "SYMBOL")

# Removing genes that are not statistically significant. 
markers <-  markers %>% dplyr::filter(p_val_adj < 0.05)
#head(markers, n = 50)

pos.markers <-  markers %>% dplyr::filter(avg_log2FC > 0) %>%  arrange(desc(abs(avg_log2FC)))
#head(pos.markers, n = 50)

pos.ranks <- pos.markers$ENTREZID[abs(pos.markers$avg_log2FC) > 0]
#head(pos.ranks)

pos_go <- enrichGO(gene = pos.ranks,           #a vector of entrez gene id
                   OrgDb = "org.Mm.eg.db",    
                   ont = "BP",
                   readable = TRUE)              #whether mapping gene ID to gene Name

pos_go
